    {
      "content": "Overview",
      "pos": [
        441,
        449
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "After you develop a web application in Visual Studio, you can publish that application more easily to an Azure cloud service by using the <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Publish Azure Application<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> wizard.",
      "pos": [
        451,
        626
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "The first section explains the steps that you must complete before you use the wizard, and the remaining sections explain the features of the wizard.",
      "pos": [
        627,
        776
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "<ph id=\"ph1\">[AZURE.NOTE]</ph> This topic is about deploying to cloud services, not to web sites.",
      "pos": [
        779,
        858
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "For information about deploying to web sites, see <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>How to Deploy an Azure Web Site<ept id=\"p1\">](https://social.msdn.microsoft.com/Search/windowsazure?query=How%20to%20Deploy%20an%20Azure%20Web%20Site&amp;Refinement=138&amp;ac=4#refinementChanges=117&amp;pageNumber=1&amp;showMore=false)</ept>.",
      "pos": [
        859,
        1118
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Prerequisites",
      "pos": [
        1123,
        1136
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Before you can publish your web application to Azure, you need to have a Microsoft account and an Azure subscription, and you have to associate your web application with an Azure cloud service.",
      "pos": [
        1138,
        1331
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "If you’ve already completed these tasks, you can skip to the next section.",
      "pos": [
        1332,
        1406
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Get a Microsoft account and an Azure subscription.",
      "pos": [
        1411,
        1461
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "You can try a free one month free Azure subscription <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>here<ept id=\"p1\">](https://azure.microsoft.com/pricing/free-trial/)</ept>",
      "pos": [
        1462,
        1570
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Create a cloud service and a storage account on Azure.",
      "pos": [
        1575,
        1629
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "You can do this from Server Explorer in Visual Studio, or by using the <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Azure Management portal<ept id=\"p1\">](http://go.microsoft.com/fwlink/?LinkID=213885)</ept>.",
      "pos": [
        1630,
        1774
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "For more information about how to set up your Azure environment, see <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Setting Up Services Required to Publish a Cloud Service from Visual Studio<ept id=\"p1\">](vs-azure-tools-publish-azure-application-wizard)</ept>.",
      "pos": [
        1775,
        1970
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Enable your web application for Azure.",
      "pos": [
        1975,
        2013
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "To enable your web application to be published to Azure from Visual Studio, you’ll need to associate it with an Azure cloud service project in Visual Studio.",
      "pos": [
        2014,
        2171
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "To create the associated cloud service project, open the shortcut menu for the project for your web application, and then choose Convert, <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Convert to Azure Cloud Service Project<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept>.",
      "pos": [
        2172,
        2353
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "After the cloud service project is added to your solution, open the same shortcut menu again and then choose <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Publish<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept>.",
      "pos": [
        2358,
        2479
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "For more information about how to enable applications for Azure, see <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>How to: Migrate and Publish a Web Application to an Azure Cloud Service from Visual Studio<ept id=\"p1\">](https://msdn.microsoft.com/library/azure/hh420322.aspx)</ept>.",
      "pos": [
        2480,
        2698
      ]
    },
    {
      "pos": [
        2701,
        2799
      ],
      "content": "<ph id=\"ph1\">[AZURE.NOTE]</ph> Be sure to start Visual Studio with administrator credentials (Run As Administrator)."
    },
    {
      "content": "When you’re ready to publish your application, open the shortcut menu for the Azure cloud service project, and then choose <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Publish<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept>.",
      "pos": [
        2804,
        2939
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "The following steps show the Publish Azure Application wizard.",
      "pos": [
        2940,
        3002
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Choosing Your Subscription",
      "pos": [
        3007,
        3033
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "To choose a subscription",
      "pos": [
        3039,
        3063
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Before you use the wizard for the first time, you must sign in.",
      "pos": [
        3068,
        3131
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Choose the <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Sign In<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> link.",
      "pos": [
        3132,
        3160
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Sign in to the Azure portal when prompted, and provide your Azure user name and password.",
      "pos": [
        3161,
        3250
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "This is one of the publishing wizard screens",
      "pos": [
        3259,
        3303
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "The list of subscriptions populates with the subscriptions associated with your account.",
      "pos": [
        3380,
        3468
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "You might also see subscriptions from any subscription files that you imported previously.",
      "pos": [
        3469,
        3559
      ]
    },
    {
      "pos": [
        3564,
        3657
      ],
      "content": "In the <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Choose your subscription<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> list, choose the subscription to use for this deployment."
    },
    {
      "content": "If you choose <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>&lt;Manage…&gt;<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept>, the <bpt id=\"p2\">**</bpt>Manage Subscriptions<ept id=\"p2\">**</ept> dialog box appears, and you can choose the subscription and user account you want to use.",
      "pos": [
        3662,
        3809
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "The <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Accounts<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> tab shows all of your accounts, and the <bpt id=\"p2\">**</bpt>Subscriptions<ept id=\"p2\">**</ept> tab shows all of the subscriptions associated with the accounts.",
      "pos": [
        3810,
        3949
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "You can also choose a region from which to use Azure resources, as well as create or import certificates for your subscription from the Azure portal.",
      "pos": [
        3950,
        4099
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "If you imported any subscriptions from a subscription file, the associated certificates will appear under the <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Certificates<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> tab.",
      "pos": [
        4100,
        4231
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "When you're done, choose the <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Close<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> button.",
      "pos": [
        4232,
        4278
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Manage subscriptions",
      "pos": [
        4286,
        4306
      ]
    },
    {
      "pos": [
        4384,
        4456
      ],
      "content": "<ph id=\"ph1\">[AZURE.NOTE]</ph> A subscription file can contain more than one subscription."
    },
    {
      "pos": [
        4461,
        4500
      ],
      "content": "Choose the <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Next<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> button to continue."
    },
    {
      "content": "If there aren't any cloud services in your subscription, you need to create a cloud service in Azure to host your project.",
      "pos": [
        4507,
        4629
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "The <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Create Cloud Service and Storage Account<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> dialog box appears.",
      "pos": [
        4630,
        4698
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Specify a new name for the cloud service.",
      "pos": [
        4704,
        4745
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "The name must be unique in Azure.",
      "pos": [
        4746,
        4779
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Then specify a region or affinity group for a data center that’s near you or most of your clients.",
      "pos": [
        4780,
        4878
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "This name is also used for a new storage account that Azure creates for your cloud service.",
      "pos": [
        4879,
        4970
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Modify any settings you want for this deployment and then publish it by choosing the <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Publish<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> button (The next section provides more details about the various settings).",
      "pos": [
        4975,
        5147
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "To review the settings before publishing, choose the <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Next<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> button.",
      "pos": [
        5148,
        5217
      ]
    },
    {
      "pos": [
        5224,
        5335
      ],
      "content": "<ph id=\"ph1\">[AZURE.NOTE]</ph> If you chose Publish in this step, you can monitor the status of this deployment in Visual Studio."
    },
    {
      "content": "You can modify both common and advanced settings for a deployment by using the <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Publish Azure Application<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> wizard.",
      "pos": [
        5337,
        5453
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "For example, you can choose a setting to deploy your application to a test environment before you release it.",
      "pos": [
        5454,
        5563
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "The following illustration shows the <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Common Settings<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> tab for an Azure deployment.",
      "pos": [
        5564,
        5649
      ]
    },
    {
