    {
      "content": "This type of deployment can be faster than a full deployment.",
      "pos": [
        8548,
        8609
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Choose the <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Settings<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> link to open the <bpt id=\"p2\">**</bpt>Deployment update settings<ept id=\"p2\">**</ept> dialog box, shown in the following illustration.",
      "pos": [
        8610,
        8730
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Deployment Settings",
      "pos": [
        8739,
        8758
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "You can choose either of two options for update deployment, incremental or simultaneous.",
      "pos": [
        8835,
        8923
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "An incremental deployment updates one deployed instance at a time, so that your application remains online and available to users.",
      "pos": [
        8924,
        9054
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "A simultaneous deployment updates all deployed instances at once.",
      "pos": [
        9055,
        9120
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Simultaneous update is faster than incremental update, but if you choose this option, your application might not be available during the update process.",
      "pos": [
        9121,
        9273
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "You should select the check box for If deployment can't be updated, do a full deployment if you want the full deployment to take place automatically if an update deployment fails.",
      "pos": [
        9279,
        9458
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "A full deployment resets the virtual IP (VIP) address for the cloud service.",
      "pos": [
        9459,
        9535
      ]
    },
